
** Undo

  - *C-u undo* performs 'selective undo'. In transient-mark if region
    is active, always 'selective undo' is used.

** Mark

  - *C-SPC* -> *C-@*
  - *C-SPC C-SPC* set the mark but not in transient mode
  - *C-u C-SPC ...* moves to previous marks
  - *M-@* mark-word

** Delete and Killing

  - *M-\* delete \s about point
  - *M-SPC* delete \s about point, leave one space
  - *C-x C-o* delete blank line
  - *M-^* delete-indentation (join lines)

  - *C-k* kill-line

** Pasting and Yanking

  - *C-y M-y* yank previous kills
  - *C-y C-u M-y* yank previous kills but first move to last yank

  - *C-u C-y* does not move point by yanking
  - *C-x C-v* find-alternate-file
  - *C-x C-v C-a C-k C-g* puts the filename of the current buffer to the
    kill ring
  - *C-u 0 C-k* kills to the beginning of the line

** Universal Arguments and Repeating

  - *C-u 3*
  - *C-u*     (C-u  4)
  - *C-u C-u* (C-u 16)
  - *M-3*     (C-u  3)
  - *M--*     (C-u -1)
  - *C-u 64 C-u 1* inserts 64 '1'

  - *C-x z(z)* repeat
  - *C-x e(e)* kbd macro
  - *C-x ESC ESC* repeat-complex-command
  - *M-x list-command-history*

** Registers

  - *C-x r SPC R* register point
  - *C-x r j R*   jump to register point

  - *C-u C-x s i R* With prefix argument deletes too the marked text

** Counting Lines

  - *M-=* count-lines-region

** Pages

  - *C-q C-l* inserts ^L

** Frames

  - *C-x 5 C-f* find-file-other-frame

** Windows

  - *C-x 0* deletes the current window.
  - *C-x ^* enlarges the current window.
  - *C-M-v*     scroll-other-window upward
  - *M-- C-M-v* scroll-other-window downward

** Commenting

  - *M-;* comment-dwim

** Eval

  - *C-x C-e* eval-last-sexp. Prints the result in the mini buffer.

** Paren

  - *C-M-n* Move forward over a parenthetical group (`forward-list').
  - *C-M-p* Move backward over a parenthetical group(`backward-list').
  - *C-M-u* Move up in parenthesis structure (`backward-up-list').
  - *C-M-d* Move down in parenthesis structure (`down-list').

  - *C-M-a* Beginning of defun
  - *C-M-e* End of defun
  - *C-M-h* Mark defun
  - *C-M-f* Move forward to the next sexp
  - *C-M-b* Move backward to the next sexp

  - *C-M-SPC* mark-sexp

** Minibuffer


** Special Characters

  - *C-x 8 C-h* list all the special characters
  - *C-x 8 C* ©

** Scroll

  - *C-v* scroll-up
  - *M-v* scroll-down
  - *C-p* previous-line
  - *C-n* next-line
  - *M-r* move-to-window-line. C-u 0 top line. C-u - bottom line.

  - C-u M-< move n/10
  - *C-x C-n* set-goal-column. Positions a fix column to which the
    cursor moves by C-n and C-p.

** Rect

  - *C-x r t* replaces rectangle content with string

** Shell

  - see EmacsShell

** Input Methods

  - *C-x 8 " s* -> ß
  - *C-x 8 " a* -> ä
  - *C-x 8 " A* -> Ä

** Fonts

  - *S-mouse1* - Font dialogs
  - *C-x C-+*  - Increases the current font
  - *C-x C--*  - Decreases the current font
  - *C-x C-0*  - Restores the default size

** Simulate Modifiers

  - C-x @ [Ssachm]
    - S shift
    - s super
    - a alt
    - c ctrl
    - h hyper
    - m meta
